  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Ezra 4:23",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Ezra 4:23",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And made them to cease by force and power — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "As they abused the king by their misinformations, in the obtaining of this order, so they abused him in the execution of it; for the order was only to prevent the building of the city and its walls. But, having power in their hands, they on this pretence stopped the building of the temple. See what need we have to pray, not only for kings, but for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "all in authority ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "under them; because the quietness of our lives depends much on the integrity and wisdom of inferior magistrates as well as the supreme.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
