        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The \"adversaries\" lost no time. Having obtained the decree which forbad further building, they proceeded with it to Jerusalem, and by a display of force compelled the Jews to submission. No doubt resistance might have been made, but resistance would have been rebellion. Ezra 4:23",
