  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The result of this royal command. As soon as the copy of the letter was read before Rehum and his associates, they went up in haste to Jerusalem to the Jews, and hindered them by violence and force. אדרע with א prosthetic only here, elsewhere דּרע ( equals  זרוע), arm, violence. Bertheau translates, \"with forces and a host;\" but the rendering of אדרע or זרוע by \"force\" can neither be shown to be correct from ",
        "children": []
      },
